---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout title="Privacy Policy — New England Crust" description="How New England Crust collects, uses, and protects your information.">
  <div class="max-w-2xl mx-auto px-6 py-16">
    <p class="text-orange-400 text-xs font-semibold tracking-widest uppercase mb-4">• Legal</p>
    <h1 class="text-4xl font-bold text-white mb-6">Privacy Policy</h1>
    <p class="text-gray-400 text-sm mb-10">Last updated: June 2026</p>

    <div class="prose prose-invert max-w-none">
      <p>New England Crust ("we," "us," or "our") operates newenglandcrust.com. This page explains what information we collect when you visit the site, how we use it, and what choices you have.</p>

      <h2>Information we collect</h2>
      <p>We do not collect personal information directly — no account registration, no contact form that stores your data on our servers. However, third-party services we use may collect information automatically when you visit:</p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Analytics.</strong> We use Google Analytics to understand how visitors find and use the site. Google Analytics collects data such as your approximate location, browser type, pages visited, and time on site. This data is aggregated and anonymous to us. You can opt out via the <a href="https://tools.google.com/dlpage/gaoptout" rel="noopener noreferrer">Google Analytics opt-out browser add-on</a>.</li>
        <li><strong>Cookies.</strong> Our site and third-party services (including Google Analytics and affiliate networks) use cookies — small text files stored in your browser — to track sessions and referrals. You can disable cookies in your browser settings, though some site features may not work correctly if you do.</li>
        <li><strong>Affiliate networks.</strong> When you click an affiliate link on this site, the retailer or affiliate network (such as Amazon Associates, Impact, or Awin) may set a tracking cookie to attribute any resulting purchase to us. These networks have their own privacy policies governing how they handle that data.</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>How we use information</h2>
      <p>Analytics data helps us understand which content is most useful and how visitors navigate the site. We use that information to write better posts and improve the site experience. We do not sell, rent, or share any personal information with third parties for their own marketing purposes.</p>

      <h2>Affiliate links</h2>
      <p>New England Crust participates in affiliate marketing programs including the Amazon Services LLC Associates Program. When you click an affiliate link and make a purchase, we may earn a small commission at no additional cost to you. Clicking these links may result in a tracking cookie being set by the retailer or affiliate network. See our <a href="/disclosure/">Affiliate Disclosure</a> for full details on how this works.</p>

      <h2>Third-party links</h2>
      <p>This site contains links to external websites — retailers, manufacturers, and other resources. We are not responsible for the privacy practices of those sites and encourage you to review their policies before sharing any personal information with them.</p>

      <h2>Children's privacy</h2>
      <p>This site is not directed at children under 13 and we do not knowingly collect personal information from children. If you believe a child has provided us with personal information, please contact us and we will delete it.</p>

      <h2>Changes to this policy</h2>
      <p>We may update this policy from time to time. When we do, we'll update the date at the top of this page. Continued use of the site after any changes constitutes your acceptance of the updated policy.</p>

      <h2>Contact</h2>
      <p>If you have questions about this privacy policy or how your information is handled, you can reach us through the <a href="/about/">About page</a>.</p>
    </div>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>
